<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n15019g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15019g">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15019g"> 19(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ravelins, / curtain, bastion</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The citadel at Dublin was designed to be a pentagon &hellip; <mark>with ramparts, ravelins, curtain, and bastions</mark>, the walls being intended of brick faced with stone, and built on a frame of timber, and piles. It was to contain barracks for 700 men and officers, with a governor&apos;s house, and store houses for munitions of war, a chapel, a prison, a clock-tower, and gateway and drawbridges similar to those at Tilbury fort and Portsmouth, the estimated cost being, &pound;131,227 5s. 9d.; the estimate for constructing a fort at Rincurran, to defend Kinsale, being &pound;10,350. <small> Charles Haliday, <a name="SKD2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SKD2"><cite title="source">The Scandinavian Kingdom of Dublin</cite></a>, 2nd ed. (1884) 230</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15195i" href="c15all.htm#c15195i">VI.C.15:195(i)</a>, <a name="c15196a" href="c15all.htm#c15196a">VI.C.15:196(a)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
